(10, '7X2N5L7T', '60 Inch Platform Tree Swing', '\"[{\"text\":\"Whether they have special needs or not, every child has sensory needs that swinging can address. We all heard about the 5 senses. But in reality, we have 8 systems that we use to help us navigate and explore our environments. When it comes to our sensory systems, swinging is a fantastic way to engage a child\\u2019s vestibular sensory system \\u2013 the ability to know how to use our muscles in correlation with gravity. This system controls behavior such as balance and movement. And swinging is a great sensory workout for kids looking to build gross motor skills and develop sensory integration. What\\u2019s more, swinging helps the brain learn to make sense of speed and direction, which may be beneficial for kids with visual perception issues.\"},{\"text\":\"Dimensions: 60 x 32 x 4.1 inches; Weight: 8.77 pounds; Maximum Weight Recommendation: 350 pounds; Material: Synthetic Polypropylene; Color: Blue\"}]\"', 149, 'toy', 'img10_7X2N5L7T.png', 'https://www.FunCultureLand.com/img/img13.png', 0, NULL, 0),
